National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan recently held a discussion with officials from the Bucharest Nine (B9) group, which consists of NATO Allies from the eastern flank. The purpose of the conversation was to provide an update on U.S. engagements with Russian officials and seek input from counterparts on matters related to Transatlantic security. During the discussion, all participants stressed the urgency for Russia to deescalate tensions at its border with Ukraine. Mr. Sullivan reiterated the United States' commitment to close coordination with Allies and partners, highlighting the importance of unity. It was also emphasized that decisions regarding their security would not be made without their involvement. Additionally, all participants expressed their unwavering commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity in the face of Russian aggression. The Bucharest Nine member countries include Bulgaria, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Romania, and Slovakia.